Siemens CFO Says Company Seeks Large Acquisitions, FT Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-02-14T00:33:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/siemens-cfo-says-company-seeks-large-acquisitions-ft-reports.html
Siemens AG is planning to make
“significant” acquisitions as it seeks to expand its power
networks and plant automation businesses, the Financial Times
reported, citing an interview with Chief Financial Officer  Joe Kaeser .  The company has reached the “management maturity” to
pursue this strategy and “when we talk about larger
acquisitions, we mean significant sums of up to several billion
euros,” Kaeser said, according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 